Steps to setup the webapp :

1) Install java : 
	- copy jdk to the prefrred location (http://www.wikihow.com/Install-Oracle-Java-JDK-on-Ubuntu-Linux)
	- add JAVA_HOME in .bashrc file 
	- complie .bashrc

2) Install maven :
	- copy maven to a preferred location
	- add M2_HOME in .bashrc file
	- complie .bashrc


3) mysql server :
	mysql -p warriorclan -u root -h localhost
	service mysql start
	service mysql stop
	service mysql restart

4) Setup webserver : Tomcat

5) Creating webapp
	- create a maven project with apache webapp archtype

6) Setting up remote debugger :
	- add this in catalina.sh 
		CATALINA_OPTS="-Xdebug -Xrunjdwp:transport=dt_socket,address=8000,server=y,suspend=n"

7) user.properties is for specying path to tomcat home directory

8) ROOT.xml : put this at con/Catalina/localhost of tomcat